LAFIA – Alhaji Usman Abdullahi, the Ohimege Opanda in Nasarawa State, has on Thursday urged the Federal Government to create more jobs to curtail incessant kidnapping and other security challenges facing the country. Abdullahi, a first class traditional ruler, made the called while fielding questions from newsmen in his palace in Umaisha, Toto Local Government Area of the state. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The monarch said that the creation of more job opportunities by the Federal Government would go a long way in not only tackling poverty in the country but will also checkmate insecurity facing the nation. “A lots needs to be done by the Federal Government to create mass employment opportunities for the jobless youths and other Nigerians. “Creation of more jobs through various programmes will go a long way in tackling insecurity thereby improving on the standard of living of people in the country,” he said. Abdullahi further appealed to Nasarawa and Kogi state governments to be liaising with each other to return the Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) in the area to their homes. He urged his subjects and other Nigerians to pray and support leaders at all levels, while urging them to live in peace and tolerate one another, irrespective of their affiliations for the overall development of the country.